<HEADLINE> French Flag Carrier on Goodwill Visit to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 27 (Xinhua) -- A flag carrier of
French naval forces arrived at Dar es Salaam port Monday for a
three-day goodwill visit to Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The captain of the ship "Le Var", Rear Admiral Patrice
Puy-Montbrun, said that the visit aims to develop links with
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
"We have a tradition to come by sea," Puy-Montbrun told a press
 conference on the 157-meter-long, 21-meter-wide ship, which has a
 displacement of 18,000 tons and a draught of 8.7 meters.
</P>
<P>
Puy-Montbrun, who is also Commander of French Fleet in the
Indian Ocean, said that the ship sailed into Tanzanian water in
the morning amid light rains.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the vessel had visited Durban port of South Africa and
the Mozambican capital Maputo.
</P>
<P>
The commander revealed that the French naval forces regularly
have over 10 ships in the Indian Ocean, adding that more ships
will be deployed if there is an emergency.
</P>
<P>
After the visit, the ship will head for Arabian countries for
other visits, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
