<HEADLINE> Tunisian PM Meets Libyan Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Tunisian Prime Minister Hamed
Karoui held a meeting here Monday evening with visiting Secretary
General of the Libyan General People's Committee (prime minister)
Mohamed Ahmed Al-Mangoush.
</P>
<P>
Al-Mangoush arrived in the Tunisian capital Monday to head his
country's delegation to the bi-annual session of the Follow-up
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The two-day session will review the implementation of the
decisions of the Tunisian-Libyan Higher Committee, the
Tunisia-Africa News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers discussed the implementation of the
cooperation program set by the 12th session of the higher joint
committee, held in Libya in February, as well as furthering
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Tunisian Minister of Industry Al-Moncef Bin Abdullah
held a working meeting with Libyan Secretary for Industry Muftah
Azouz. The two sides discussed progress of the bilateral
cooperation in the field of industry.
</P>
<P>
The trade exchanges between Tunisia and Libya increased by 22
percent over the last eight months, compared with the similar
period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
