<HEADLINE> Ecuador' Government Assumes Control of Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, September 27 (Xinhua)-- Ecuador's government assumed
Monday control of Popular Bank, which is undergoing financial
hardships.
</P>
<P>
This measure intends to clear the finance of one of the
largest private credit institutions in the country and to protect
clients' savings, said authorities of the Banking Committee.
</P>
<P>
Administration of Popular Bank was taken over by state Agency
for Deposit Guarantee, which is controlling banks with financial
difficulties in the country.
</P>
<P>
Authorities from the Bank Committee said they'd deepen
investigations regarding the bank's financial situation, which
will keep on going.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12 banks have collapsed in Ecuador in the country's
worst economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador, slumped in its worst economic crisis in decades, has
said it cannot service its 13 billion-dollar foreign debt which
takes up more than half of its budget each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
