<HEADLINE> 9 killled in Colombian Wave of Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- An armed group
murdered Monday seven persons in Santander department, Colombia,
while a couple were murdered by hired killers in Antioquia
department, said police Monday.
</P>
<P>
The assassination of seven people was registered at
Barrancabermeja city (Santander), northern Colombia, and was
attributed by police to right-wing paramilitaries.
</P>
<P>
This Monday's killings are the fourth carried out so far this
year in Barrancaabermeja, where in 1998 a single entry of
paramilitaries left 13 locals murdered.
</P>
<P>
Paramilitary organization United Autodefenses of Colombia (AUC)
have claimed so far this year the murder of dozens of persons
accused of being guerrilla collaborators.
</P>
<P>
In Envigado locality (Antioquia), a Dutchman and his Colombian
wife were shot to death in their car by a group of at least four
hitmen that rode a motorcycle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
