<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Ready to Curb Outbreak of Malaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Health
Ministry said here Monday that necessary medical drugs and medical
equipment have been prepared to contain possible malaria outbreak
in the country this year.
</P>
<P>
Alemayehu Seyfu, chief of Epidemiology and AIDS Department of
the Health Ministry, said anti-mosquito chemicals have been
sprayed on malaria-prone areas of the country to prevent the
possible flare up of the epidemic particularly from September to
November.
</P>
<P>
Malaria is one of the major killer diseases in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that some 40 million Ethiopians, or two-thirds
of the country's 60 million population, are threatened by malaria.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government has pledged about 10 million U.S.
dollars for the malaria control program in the 1999/2000 fiscal
year, up from last year' s budget of about four million U.S.
dollars. 
