<HEADLINE> S. African Politicians Shocked By Tourist Bus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 27 (Xinhua) -- South African
politicians expressed shock at the death oeremy Cronin, chairman of the National
 Assembly's transport
portfolio committee, said he was deeply shocked by the incident,
which came so soon after four other serious bus crashes.
</P>
<P>
He extended the committee's condolences to the families of the
26 victims, and to the12 other tourists who were injured.
</P>
<P>
Cronin said the accident highlighted the need for the
high-level summit on road safety proposed by Transport Minister
Dullah Omar.
</P>
<P>
"It clearly underlines the need to look firstly at enforcing
safety regulations, and also increasing capacity to enforce those
regulations," he said.
</P>
<P>
There is a great dearth of traffic officials on the road, for
which the provinces have been blaming the national government and
vice versa. Whatever the case is, the country has to find the will
to resource the measures that are needed for greater safety and
enforcement, Cronin said.
