<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Malian Defense Ministers Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor and
Defense Minister Chi Haotian held talks with Malian Defense
Minister Mohamed Salia Sokona here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
said that the two countries share sustained and stable development
of friendly cooperation since bilateral ties were forged 27 years
ago. The two sides have witnessed fruitful cooperation in
political, economic, military and cultural areas, he added.
</P>
<P>
China and Mali have similar points of view on major
international issues, he said, adding that China appreciates the
Malian Government's "one China" stand and support of China on
human rights issues.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the two armies have maintained satisfactory exchanges
and cooperation, and the frequent exchanges of high-level visits
have helped promote mutual understanding and friendship between
the two armies, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Chi reiterated China's principled position on the Taiwan issue
and said that the People's Liberation Army has the will and power
to safeguard the sovereignty and territorial integrity of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Sokona expressed satisfaction with Mali-China relations, saying
that the two countries have common interests and understanding on
major world issues, frequent two-way visits and sound cooperation
in many areas.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also exchanged views on world and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Chi presided over a welcoming ceremony for
Sokona.  
</P>
</TEXT>
