<HEADLINE> Vice Premier: China Values Foreign Experts' Efforts (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The vice premier said that China had encountered a series of
complicated domestic and international events during the past year,
and has maintained social stability and promoted economic growth.
After reaping a good summer harvest, the country now has a good
autumn harvest in sight, he added.
</P>
<P>
Also, state-owned enterprises has made further progress in
shaking off their difficulties, the strategies for revitalizing
the nation by reliance on science and education, and for
sustainable development, have been executed smoothly, while
reforms in all fields has been advancing in perfect order, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people of all ethnic groups, under the leadership
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China with
Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core, are marching toward the new
century full of confidence, said the vice premier.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan, he pointed out, is an inalienable part of the sacred
territory of China, adding that "the Taiwan compatriots are our
own flesh and blood." He extended deep sympathy and solicitude
for the Taiwan compatriots who have suffered from the recent
disastrous earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
"In the past few days," he said, "we have shown great concern
over the disaster, and provided all possible aid to Taiwan
compatriots in various forms, and hope we can help mitigate their
losses as we express our deepest sympathy."
</P>
<P>
We will, as always, adhere to the basic principle of "peaceful
reunification" and "one country, two systems," and the eight-
points proposition put forward by President Jiang Zemin, to
continually promote the development of the relations between the
two sides across the Taiwan Straits and the reunification of the
motherland, he emphasized.
</P>
</TEXT>
