<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 152,797 Persons Arrested In Operation by Bangladeshi Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September (Xinhua) -- A total of 152,797 persons have so
far been arrested and 2,832 illegal arms seized in Bangladesh from
across the country since the countrywide combing operation by
police, the Bangladesh Rifles and Ansar began on April 23.
</P>
<P>
Of the arrest, 23,521 persons were held from Dhaka metropolis
with 377 illegal weapons and 693 rounds of bullet, Bangladesh News
Agency reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
From Dhaka range 30,583 persons including 19,279 wanted accused
were arrested with 280 illegal weapons and 1,224 rounds of bullet,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to the Bangladesh Observer, an English newspaper, the
special anti-crime drives of combined forces "looked like a
foredoomed exercise as most of those caught came out on bail hours
after arrest". 
</P>
</TEXT>
