<HEADLINE> Over 1,800 Journalists to Report National Day Celebration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,800 domestic and
foreign journalists have applied to report the grand celebration
of the 50th anniversary of the People's Republic of China, a
senior Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Among them, some 850 are mainland journalists, 221 from the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), Macao and Taiwan,
and more than 730 are foreign journalists.
</P>
<P>
"We sincerely welcome overseas journalists to report our
National Day celebrations, and hope that our friends will share
our happiness," said Liang Guihe, director of the press center for
the celebration of the anniversary, at a reception party held this
evening for both domestic and foreign journalists.
</P>
<P>
The press center officially went into operation on September 20
and is responsible for journalist's applications, the distribution
of press credentials, and providing information.  
</P>
