<HEADLINE> Vice Premier: China Values Foreign Experts' Efforts (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Looking ahead to the 21st century, Li said, China will continue
to expand its political, economic, scientific, technological,
educational, and cultural exchanges with other countries on the
basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
As an important part of China's reform and open-up policy, the
vice premier noted, China will continue to strengthen the
introduction of foreign talents and expand personnel exchanges and
cooperation with governments and non-governmental organizations of
different countries. China will also continue to give full play to
the role of its own personnel and simultaneously continue to seek
help from foreign experts, Li added.
</P>
<P>
China will also create favorable working conditions and a
convenient living environment for foreign experts working in China,
help them play their roles to the full, and safeguard their
legitimate rights and interests so that the work of international
personnel exchange will continue to contribute to the promotion of
friendship between the Chinese people and people from other
countries, said the vice premier.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,800 Chinese and foreign guests, including more than 1,
000 foreign experts and 100 Friendship Award winners, attended the
reception.  
</P>
