<HEADLINE> Highlights of Today's Diplomatic News in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights
of the diplomatic news in China released by Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
 President Jiang Zemin Meets Head of Time Warner
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin met today in Shanghai with a
delegation of the Time Warner Inc., led by Gerald Levin, the
company's chairman and chief executive officer, who is in Shanghai
for the current Fortune Global Forum.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the forum, which begins today, is "China: the Next
50 Years." During the session, foreign and Chinese participants
and experts will hold extensive discussions on issues concerning
China's current situation and future development.
</P>
<P>
 President Jiang Meets Executives of International
Companies
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin today met with scores of foreign
businessmen who are in Shanghai to attend the '99 Fortune Global
Forum that begins today.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 businessmen, including those from near 60 out of
the Fortune top 500, have signed in to attend the forum, which
will last through September 29.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese President Meets Singaporean Visitor
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin told Lee Kuan Yew, senior
minister of Singapore, that countries with different values should
pursue common ground while reserving differences.
</P>
<P>
He said that at the turn of the century, all countries aspire
after peace and development, so it is very important for countries
to reach mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also expressed his satisfaction with the development of
Sino-Singaporean ties in recent years, saying that it is of great
significance that the leaders of the two countries exchange views
frequently on international and regional issues, especially on the
development trend of international economy and finance.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Premier Meets Former Tanzanian President
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said in a meeting here today with
former Tanzanian President Ali Hassan Mwinyi, that the Chinese
government highly treasures the friendship between the two
countries, adding that in the more than 30 years since the
establishment of diplomatic ties, bilateral cooperation has
witnessed smooth development.
</P>
</TEXT>
