<HEADLINE> 11 People Killed in Road Accidents in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed and
over 50 others were injured in separate road accidents in
Bangladesh on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Eight people were killed and about 30 others were injured
Monday night when a bus fell into a roadside ditch near the
Bangabandhu Bridge, in northwestern Bangladesh, the Bangladesh TV
reported.
</P>
<P>
All the dead were passengers sitting on the roof of the bus,
and the injured were rushed to nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
In other three separate road accidents in the southeastern
Chittagong district, three persons, including a minor girl, were
killed and 22 others were injured on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway,
the BSS reported. 
</P>
