<HEADLINE> 3.2 Million Angolans Badly Need Emergent Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- A senior Angolan official
announced here on Monday that in his country, the number of the
people in dire need of emergent assistance is about 3.2 million.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, there exist over two million displaced people
living in abject poverty due to the endless civil war.
</P>
<P>
Albino Malungo, minister of Assistance and Social
Reintegration, told the press that the deteriorating situation in
the provinces all over his country, especially in Malanje, Huambo,
Bie, Cuando Cubango, Moxico, Lunda- norte, Lunda-sul and Luanda,
requires emergent assistance or a humanitarian intervention.
</P>
<P>
Every day, dozens of families in "extremely difficult
situation" arrive in the capital city of Luanda. And at this
moment, there are more than 500, 000 displaced people without
assistance in the city with a total population of three million,
according to the minister.
</P>
<P>
Malungo also announced an increase of the amount of the flights
with humanitarian aid for the interior part of the country, adding
that the government is making efforts to help the poor residents
in the interior Angola and the Province of Bie.
</P>
<P>
He lamented that the trucks circulating between Benguela and
Bie are exposed to attacks by the "armed band" of Jonas Savimbi,
referring to the rebel National Union for Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA), but assured that "everything is ready" for giving
Bie the maximum assistance.
</P>
<P>
With the help of international humanitarian organizations, the
Angolan government will succeed in providing the residents in the
Bie Province with seeds and farming utensils, said the minister.
</P>
</TEXT>
