<HEADLINE> Loroupe Attacks Denyan Athletics Federation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan women runner Tegla
Loroup, who won the Berlin marathon race with the world best time
on Sunday, attacked the Kenyan Athletics Federation Monday over
its treatment of women athletes.
</P>
<P>
"They just don't care about women. They only added me to the
World Championship's team two weeks before Seville, and that was
only because Nike paid my fare. That made only six Kenyan women
altogether in Seville," said Loroupe, who has confirmed to take
part in the London marathon on April 16 next year.
</P>
<P>
"I would like them to tell me now that I'm selected for Sydney,
so that I can prepare properly," she added in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Loroupe clocked two hours 20 minutes 43 seconds in Berlin to
better her own world mark set in Rotterdam last year by four
seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
