<HEADLINE> Vice Premier: China Values Foreign Experts' Efforts (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 27 (Xinhua)-- China values the contributions
made by foreign experts to China's construction in all spheres,
said Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China,
made the remark today at the National Day reception in honor of
foreign experts and hosted by the State Bureau of Foreign Experts
Affairs at the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the government of the People's Republic of China
and Premier Zhu Rongji, Li expressed his warm welcome and extended
his sincere regards to all the foreign experts, overseas Chinese
experts, and international friends participating in, concerning
with and rendering support to the Chinese revolution and
modernization.
</P>
<P>
He noted that among the foreign experts present, some are old
friends and old comrades who came to China prior to or in the
early period of the founding of New China, adding that the
majority are new friends who came to China to help Chinese people
with their work after the policy of reform and opening to the
outside world was introduced.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the past 50 years, over 800,000 foreign
experts have come to China to work. "All of you are witnesses to
the brilliant history of New China. You have worked
conscientiously and with a high sense of duty," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, the achievements made by China in all spheres
of endeavor also include the fruits of the foreign experts'
diligent work.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his heartfelt thanks to the foreign experts on
behalf of the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
"Meanwhile, I hope that you will continue to cooperate closely
with your Chinese colleagues, work conscientiously, and make even
greater achievements," said the vice premier.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
