<HEADLINE> President Jiang Meets Leaders of International Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 27 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin met
here today with scores of foreign businesspeople who are attending
the '99 Fortune Global Forum which began today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the event will have a positive impact on the
development of China and the world. He said that well-known
business leaders coming from across the world to join economists
and leaders of relevant Chinese departments for discussing the
development of China and its influence on world economy provides
an opportunity for cooperation at the time of the 50th anniversary
of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 businesspeople, including those from nearly 60 of
the Fortune magazine top 500, are attending the forum, which will
last through September 29.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said that over the past 50 years,
especially the past 20 years, China has scored major achievements
in its modernization drive. History has proved that the socialist
road charted by Deng Xiaoping of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics is the development road suitable for China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China will carry out more reforms and opening
wider to the outside world. He urged Chinese firms to test their
ability and get to know the international market.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, China welcomes more overseas investment
and hopes that overseas entrepreneurs will actively participate in
competition on an equal footing.
</P>
<P>
The businesspeople extended their warm congratulations on the
50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China,
and expressed their deep appreciation for the achievements China
has made since the beginning of reform and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
They also displayed great enthusiasm for further cooperation
with Chinese partners.
</P>
<P>
About 50 chairmen of the board and CEOs of such big names as GM,
Ford, GE, Volkswagen, National, Fiat, AT&AMP;T, and Sinochem were
among those participating in the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
