<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Open Telecommunications Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia will open its
telecommunications sector to private firms in hope to speed up the
industry' s development, a senior official said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Girma Birru, minister of Economic Development and Cooperation,
said at a meeting of the Ethiopian Telecommunications Corporation
(ETC) that the government has decided to work with potential
entrepreneurs having a small share to boost the communications
sector in the country.
</P>
<P>
Working in partnership with enterprises known for their
managerial expertise, technology and capital can improve the
quality and services of this sector, he said.
</P>
<P>
Observers noticed that Ethiopia made the announcement when the
state- owned telecommunications corporation was reportedly facing
financial problems and being criticized for its low efficiency and
poor management.
</P>
<P>
It was reported in late August that of all 13,000 mobile phone
subscribers in Ethiopia, 6,000 had cancelled their subscriptions
in ETC due to high tariff and high down payments of the cellphone
service.
</P>
<P>
Cellphone service is only available in Addis Ababa, the capital
of Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
