<HEADLINE> Colombian Rebels Condition Peace Talks with Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAFE DE BOGOTA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The National
Liberation Army (ELN), Colombia's second guerrilla force, Monday
suggested the government start a "politics of reciprocal gestures"
to achieve peace.
</P>
<P>
In a statement from Venezuelan capital city of Caracas to
Colombia's radio stations, Victor Orlando, one of ELN's leaders,
said Monday the guerrillas could free some of the 63 persons his
