<HEADLINE> Sensex Rises in Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive Index
(SENSEX) rose 17.75 points Tuesday on the Bombay Stock Exchange
(BSE) on good buying support that was confined to transfer of
position by operators coupled with selective purchases from
Foreign Institutional Investors
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share sensitive index opened marginally down at
4701.19 and later moved in a restricted range of 4738.81 and
4656.44 before closing at 4733.42 as against Monday's close of
4715.67, netting a modest gain of 17.75 points.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 Index eased by 7.02 points to 2212.39 from previous
close of 2219.41.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 Index and the Dollex were quoted marginally down at
509.42 and 194.66 compared with previous close of 510.87 and
195.21 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 Index moved down by 3.20 points to 1509.65 from
Monday's close of 1512.85. 
</P>
