<HEADLINE> Turkey, Czech Sign Deal on Defense Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Turkey and the Czech Republic
on Tuesday signed an agreement on defense industry cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The deal was signed at the 4th International Defense Industry
and Navigation (IDEF '99) in Ankara by Turkish Defense Minister
Sabahattin Cakmakoglu and visiting Czech Defense Minister
Vladimir Vetchy.
</P>
<P>
Cakmakoglu said at the signing ceremony that the agreement will
lay a foundation for the exchange of defense products between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Czech signed a cooperation agreement in the fields
of military education, technology and science in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Turkey plans to sell F-16 fighter jets to Czech in the near
future, said the Turkish minister.
</P>
<P>
The IDEF '99 opened Tuesday morning and will end on Friday.
</P>
