<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodian PM Spokes Highly of China's Successes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 28 (Xinhua) -- More than 400 people
gathered happily together Tuesday evening at the Chinese Embassy
here to cerebrate the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Attending the grand reception were President of the National
Assembly Prince Norodom Ranariddh, Prime Minister Hun Sen and
other government ministers and senior officials, as well as
ambassadors from other countries.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Hun Sen, in his congratulatory speech, highly
valued China's development and achievements in the past 50 years,
saying that "China's success is a great contribution to the whole
world, including Cambodia."
</P>
<P>
"Since the founding of the People's Republic of China 50 years
ago, China, under the wise leadership of the Communist Party and
its leaders as well as the decades of hardwork of the Chinese
people, has changed greatly and its rapid development has
attracted worldwide attention," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke highly of "China's correct foreign policy" that
is to maintain the world peace, respect other countries'
independence, territorial integrity and sovereignty, insist on the
peaceful coexistence, and promote the cooperation among countries.
</P>
<P>
"The facts have proved that China's success in reform and other
fields is a valuable experience to Cambodia and other countries,"
Hun Sen stressed.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister, meanwhile, reiterated Cambodia's One China
policy, saying "Cambodia will never change its stance and will
always stick to One China policy as we enter the new century."
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Yan Tingai gave a warm welcome to the
attendance. He said that "the friendly cooperation between China
and Cambodia proved to be time-tested, despite the ever-changing
international situation in the past 50 years."
</P>
<P>
He thanked the precious sympathy and support that the King, the
Cambodian government and people extended to China's cause of
building socialism and its fight for defending the state
sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
"after 50 years of repeated exploration and on the basis of
summing up both the positive and negative experiences from itself
and others, China has found the proper way for national
rejuvenation in accordance with the national conditions of China,"
Yan said.
</P>
<P>
"As the result, the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics was created. Under the guidance of the banner of
this theory, the Chinese people showed great power of cohesion and
creation. The Chinese economy entered a new period of sustainable,
rapid and coordinated development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Both the prime minister and the ambassador very much valued the
traditional and friendly Sino-Cambodian ties that were fostered by
King Norodom Sihanouk and older generations of Chinese leaders.
</P>
<P>
They expressed full confidence in the future relations, saying
the friendly cooperation between the two countries based on the
five principles of peaceful coexistence will certainly be further
developed and consolidated in the new century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
