<HEADLINE> New Subway Line Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A new subway section running
from Fuxingmen to Bawangfen and passing through the busiest area
of Beijing became operational today.
</P>
<P>
Wen Jiabao, vice-premier and member of both the Political
Bureau and the Secretariat of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Central Commission, Jia Qinglin, secretary of the Beijing
municipal committee of the CPC, Liu Qi, mayor of Beijing, and
Sakutaro Tanino, Japanese ambassador to China, all attended the
opening ceremony for the subway section today.
</P>
<P>
The subway will help lighten traffic on the city's east-west
axis and provide service for all of Chang'an Avenue, the city's
main east-west corridor, Mayor Liu Qi said.
</P>
<P>
The subway section is 13.5 kilometers long and has 11 stations.
Electric-powered domestically made locomotives will serve on the
line.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the new line began on July 15, 1989, and a
one-stop section opened in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Now there are two operational subway lines which intersect at
Fuxingmen, and the total length of Beijing's subway system is now
54 kilometers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
