<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, September 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian jets launched fresh air strikes on the
breakaway republic of Chechnya Tuesday, the sixth consecutive day
of an intensive campaign aimed at rooting out Islamic militants
there, Russian media reported.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen sorties were flown Monday night and Tuesday morning
against infrastructure targets being used by Chechen militants for
their own ends. (Russia-Chechnya-Attacks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- At least 11 army soldiers and Tamil rebels were
killed in the latest fighting in northern Sri Lanka, military
officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry said four army soldiers were killed
Tuesday morning when Tamil rebels ambushed a route clearing patrol
in Trincomalee district, 250 kilometers northeast of Colombo. (
Sri Lanka-Fighting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KIBBUTZ EN ZIWAN, Golan Heights -- Since Shsehf Sror bought a
supermarket and a cafeteria from the collective farm Kibbutz on
the Golan Heights six months ago, he has been wondering how long
he can keep them.
</P>
<P>
As Israel is warming up for resuming peace talks with Syria,
Sror said he would not be surprised if being told some day to
abandon the kibbutz. "If the government decides to give the Golan
back to Syria for peace, then we will have to leave," Sror said.
(Israel-Syria)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- An unspecific number of Iraqi prisoners of war (POWs)
are to be released unilaterally by Iran on Wednesday, it was
announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier Mohammad Balar, the spokesman and head of the Public
Relations and Publicity Department of POWs Commissions, said that
the Iraqi POWs will be released on the occasion of 100th birth
anniversary of late Iranian spiritual leader Imam Khomeini.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqis will be released in the presence of a red cross
representative. (Iran-Iraq-POWs)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli jet fighters conducted more air raids
against the Hezbollah targets inside the security zone in South
Lebanon Tuesday morning and all fighters returned to their base
safely, the Israel Defense Force (IDF) said.
</P>
<P>
The IDF Air Force fighters struck several Hezbollah targets in
the eastern sector of the security zone and caused considerable
damage to the targets, the IDF added. (Israel-Hezbollah)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on Tuesday
voiced concern over the "usefulness" of a group of countries
working to end the fighting in Afghanistan, saying he would review
the UN's approach to the Afghan conflict.
</P>
<P>
"The unabated external involvement in the Afghan conflict leads
me to raise the question of the role of the 'six plus two group'",
said Annan in a report obtained by the press this morning. The
group, which includes Afghanistan's six neighbors, the Russia
Federation and the United States, was originally established to
adopt a joint strategy for a peaceful solution to the Afghan
conflict. (Annan-Afghanistan) 
</P>
</TEXT>
