<HEADLINE> EDS-More Added National Day Evening Party Held In Beijing (More Added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A grand evening party to mark
the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of
China was held tonight at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Top Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li
Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing were among the 8,
000-strong audience at the party with the theme: Ode to the
Motherland.
</P>
<P>
A dance drama depicting a group of veteran Chinese
revolutionaries who sacrificed their lives to found New China,
along with other song-and-dance performances were broadcast live
in China and abroad by China Central Television.
</P>
<P>
Intensively permeated with patriotic fervor, the performers
sang the praises of national independence and the opening-up and
reform policies, and reflected the Chinese people's prospects for
a bright future. Red flags, phantasmagorical backgrounds and
colorful laser beams decorated the huge stage.
</P>
<P>
The two-hour-long party involved some 2,100 performers from
more than 60 central and local theater troupes.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the performances tonight are encores of popular
numbers of the past 50 years, and we have been rehearsing them for
half a year," said the director, Zhao An.
</P>
<P>
The performances received enthusiastic applause from the
audience. After the final curtain, Jiang Zemin and other leaders
went on stage to congratulate the entertainers for their fine
performances.
</P>
<P>
The event was jointly organized by the Publicity Department of
the Communist Party of China Central Committee, the Ministry of
Culture, the State Administration of Radio, Film and Television,
the Chinese People's Liberation Army General Political Department,
and the Beijing municipal government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
