<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Police Quiz 16 Bank Workers over Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian police have
started questioning 16 people in connection with theft and fraud
at the National Bank of Commerce NBC (1997) Limited, local
newspaper "The Guardian" reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A senior police officer was quoted as saying that the suspects,
who were all former employees of the bank, allegedly have caused
losses of billions of Tanzanian shillings (one US dollar equals
800 Tanzanian shillings) by theft and fraud since January.
</P>
<P>
Simon Mwageni, Senior Assistant Commissioner of Police of the
Criminal Investigation Department, said the NBC (1997) Ltd
Managing Director, Gerald Jordan, had already submitted some
evidence concerning losses in 34 bank branches.
</P>
<P>
However, Mwageni refused to disclose the exact amount of losses
that the bank incurred but insisted that the investigators were
doing a good job.
</P>
<P>
"What I can assure you is that the suspects will never escape,"
he added. 
</P>
