<HEADLINE> Canadian Air Attendants Contract TB From Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Montreal-based charter
airline, Royal Airlines, has confirmed that six of its 158 flight
attendants are suffering from TB as a result of ferrying Kosovar
refugees.
</P>
<P>
The CTV Tuesday quoted a 38-year-old TB victim as blaming the
federal government for not warning her of such risks during the
mission.
</P>
<P>
The six, two men and four women, have been off their jobs and
undergoing treatment since early June.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the Canadian Health Department has stated that there
is little chance of an outbreak of the disease although there has
been an overly fearful response to the TB reports.
</P>
<P>
Royal Airlines made some 23 flights to Kosovar to bring about 5,
000 refugees to Canada. A handful of refugees with TB were
identified soon after their arrival, earlier media reports said.
</P>
