<HEADLINE> President: Turkey Committed to Establishing Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel said here on Tuesday that Turkey is committed to peace,
rather than war.
</P>
<P>
"The weapons which were used for war will be used to provide
peace, " Demirel said at the opening ceremony of the 4th
International Defense Industry and Navigation Fair (IDEF 99) in
Ankara.
</P>
<P>
Demirel said that if the balance can be preserved well, the
sufferings of the 20th century will not be repeated in the coming
centuries.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 60-70 million people lost their lives and many cities
and countries were destroyed in the first and second World Wars,
he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The president said the armed forces and defense industry of
Turkey is for deterrence, to provide peace in the region and to
serve peace in the world.
</P>
<P>
A total of 150 foreign companies from 25 countries and 52
local firms are represented at the IDEF 99, which was opened
Tuesday morning and will end on October 1. 
