<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Stresses Importance of Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
today stressed the importance of Beijing's environmental
protection and pollution control work during his inspection tour.
</P>
<P>
Zhu urged the local government to continue its effort to keep
clear skies and clean water, and speed up developing the city into
a highly civilized metropolis.
</P>
<P>
Beijing initiated a seven-year pollution control project for
its rivers and lakes in 1998, which is expected to cost a total of
16.5 million yuan. The first phase of the project was finished
recently, covering one billion square meters of water area.
</P>
<P>
Since 1998, the city has carried out a series of drives on the
control of vehicle exhaust emissions, reducing air pollution to
the lowest level in 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also inspected sample buses that run on natural gas, and
visited the Gaobeidian Sewage Plant, largest in China with a daily
handling capacity of one million cubic meters of sewage, or 40
percent of the total sewage volume in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Zhu visited Wangjing, the city's largest
residential quarter, and some street reconstruction projects
around the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
