<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception in Honor of Overseas Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan
today reiterated that there is only one China in the world, and
Taiwan is a part of Chinese territory, and the territory and
sovereignty of China cannot be divided.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a reception in honor of overseas Chinese
on the eve of the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People'
s Republic of China on October 1.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that the Chinese nationality advocates unification
and opposes separation, adding that the compatriots across the
Taiwan Straits are born from the same ancestors, which separatist
forces cannot resist.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed solicitude for the suffering of Taiwan
compatriots caused by the recent devastating earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
All ethnic groups, under the leadership of the Communist Party
of China, have worked together to make a poor and backward China
become a prosperous, strong, and vigorous China over the past five
decades, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
He added that Hong Kong has remained prosperous and stable
since it returned to the motherland more than two years ago, and
Macao will also return to the motherland on December 20.
</P>
<P>
This is another important event in the cause of China's
reunification, Tang said, adding that the Chinese people both at
home and overseas should be proud of it.
</P>
<P>
Anna Chan Chennault, a notable Chinese-American, said on the
occasion that overseas Chinese are very excited about the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, as
they are linked with the motherland from the bottom of their
hearts wherever they are.
</P>
<P>
She said that overseas Chinese will continue to contribute to
China's development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
