<HEADLINE> Chinese Jilin Art Ensemble Premieres in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 28 (Xinhua) -- An art ensemble of Jilin
province of China staged its first performance at the National
Theater here Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
First Secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and Development
Council Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt, five ministers including
Minister of Culture U Win Sein, and Yangon Mayor U Ko Lay as well
as Chinese Ambassador Liang Dong and foreign diplomats in Myanmar
watched the show.
</P>
<P>
The performance by the Jilin art ensemble covered "Mongolian
Dance", "Jilin Opera Highlights", "Manchu Nationality Dance" and
"Korean Nationality Dance".
</P>
<P>
The brilliant performance won applause from 1,500 audiences.
</P>
<P>
The 30-member Jilin art ensemble arrived here earlier Sunday
for a 10-day performance in Myanmar at the invitation of the
Myanmar Ministry of Culture under the cultural exchange program
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is the first leg of the four-Southeast-Asian-country
trip of the Jilin art ensemble. They will proceed to Cambodia,
Laos and Vietnam for more performances after visiting Myanmar.
</P>
