<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-28 12:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Conducts More Jet Raids in Security Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Israeli jet fighters
conducted more air raids against the Hezbollah targets inside the
security zone in South Lebanon Tuesday morning and all fighters
returned to their base safely, the Israel Defense Force (IDF) said.
</P>
<P>
The IDF Air Force fighters struck several Hezbollah targets in
the eastern sector of the security zone and caused considerable
damage to the targets, the IDF added.
</P>
<P>
The air strikes were conducted following more military attacks
against the positions of the Israeli-allied South lebanese Army
(SLA) earlier, as the IDF said, and 45-year-old Fawzi Sagghir,
chief of the SLA intelligence in the central sector of the
security zone, was killed Monday in a roadside bomb explosion. The
IDF and SLA blamed Hezbollah, or Party of God, for carrying out
this attack.
</P>
<P>
The incident triggered an almost day-long mortar, rocket and
artillery battle between Hezbollah and SLA and IDF inside the
security zone, accompanied by IDF's air raids.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister Office (PMO) on Tuesday criticized Syria
for not stopping the Hezbollah in carrying out attacks against
the SLA as well as its attacks on SLA civilian targets in the
security zone.
</P>
<P>
The escalation of fighting inside the security zone showed
Syria is not ready to resume peace talks with Israel, a PMO
official told the Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
The IDF said it took a very grave view of the wounding of
Lebanese civilians and damage to their property and noted that it
was yet another "flagrant violation" by the Hezbollah side of the
Grapes of Wrath cease-fire understanding signed in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the self-proclaimed security zone in South Lebanon
in 1985 and since then, Hezbollah and other local military groups
have been waging resistance against the Israeli occupation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
