<HEADLINE> 300 Taliban Killed in Kunduz Fighting: Afghan Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Afghan opposition Tuesday
claimed that some 300 Taliban troops have been killed while scores
of others injured in the last four days of fighting in the
northern province of Kunduz.
</P>
<P>
Despite the loss of a number of towns in the province to the
control of Taliban forces, fighting continues to rage in
Dasht-i-Archi, opposition spokesman General Hussain Anwari said
in a statement reaching here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Taliban sources had claimed to have captured the towns of Sahih
and Dasht-i-Archi, which the opposition had admitted on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Anwari said Kunduz's flat terrain will leave the Taliban
vulnerable over the coming days and so they do not view the loss
of some territory in the province as serious.
</P>
<P>
Additional opposition troops have been sent to the province to
assist in the defense of key posts there, he added.
</P>
<P>
The ruling Taliban militia launched a major offensive in Kunduz
and neighboring Samangan province on Saturday against the
opposition. 
