<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Set Up Second Private EPZ </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's second private
export processing zone (EPZ) will be set up in the country's
southeastern Chittagong district soon, the official BSS news
agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina will lay the foundation stone of
the second private EPZ on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The EPZ will be constructed on 121 hectares of land on the
northern bank of the Karnaphuli River in the district, five
kilometers off the Bangladesh Institute of Technology.
</P>
<P>
A private company will spend 2 billion taka (40 million U.S.
dollars) for the development of infrastructure at the EPZ and the
site development work is expected to start in November this year.
</P>
<P>
Some 250 industrial units could be accommodated at the EPZ,
which is expected to create employment for 50,000 people when the
industries in the zone go into production, the BSS said.
</P>
<P>
The first private EPZ, a Korean export processing zone, is
being constructed on the other side of the Karnaphuli River.
</P>
<P>
There are two EPZs in the country at present, one in the
capital city, Dhaka, and the other in the seaport city of
Chittagong and they are employing more than 81,000 people.
</P>
</TEXT>
