<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Star East Information
Technology Corp. (Star East IT) announced here Tuesday the launch
of its interactive entertainment web site -- StarEastNet.com, with
its strategic partner, IBM China/Hong Kong Limited.
</P>
<P>
Based on IBM's e-business solution, the web site leads the
world in e-entertainment transformation and provides an
interactive channel for the global Chinese community to the world
of Asian entertainment and lifestyle, said Star East It in a
statement announcing the launch of the site.
</P>
<P>
The site provides open and interactive windows of communication
from people to people, especially from artists to the public.
</P>
<P>
Running on an IBM RS/600 server, the web site will feature
updated entertainment news, official artists profile, art and
entertainment, on-line games, on-line and off-line interactive
events, city guides, live broadcasts from Star East Entertainment
Complexes, real time on-line chat between artists and fans, new
star recruitment and freebies.
</P>
<P>
Content of the web site is first presented in Cantonese and
will subsequently be in Putonghua (Mandarin) and English to reach
Chinese communities everywhere in the world.
</P>
<P>
Among the executive directors of the company are famous Hong
Kong artists Alan Tam Wing Lun, Eric Tsang Chi Wai, Natalis Chan
Pak Cheung and Jing Wong Yat Cheng.
</P>
<P>
So far, in addition to its artist shareholders, agreements have
been signed with more than 70 artists to develop their own web
pages, in an effort to make StarEastNet.com the leading
destination site for the Asian entertainment industry.
</P>
<P>
The company will focus its efforts on e-business and has plans
to include international stars to expand the market
internationally. 
