<HEADLINE> HK Sets Up Call Center Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Call Center
Association (CCA), which provides a platform for sharing
experience and disseminating the latest technologies for call
center professionals, was launched here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inauguration ceremony, Henry Ching, branch
director of the Hong Kong Productivity Council (HKPC), said call
centers have grown in importance with an increasing focus on front-
line marketing and customer services.
</P>
<P>
"Practitioners of the call center industry must proactively
conduct telemarketing and turn these data into relevant
information for strategic planning by management," he added.
</P>
<P>
"Recent surveys indicated that Asia-Pacific is the fastest
growing call center region in the world, with call center agent
jobs growing from 24,000 in 1993 to 94,000 in 1997, reflecting an
annual increase of 41 percent," he noted.
</P>
<P>
With administrative support from HKPC, the CCA is a non-profit
association that promotes excellence in three key business areas --
process improvement, people management and technology, according
to Lynda Janas, chairwoman of CCA.
</P>
<P>
Major activities of CCA will include exhibitions, benchmarking
exercises, training programs and industry surveys, she said,
adding that CCA welcomes participants from Hong Kong, as well as
call center practitioners in the vicinity of Macao and south China.
</P>
