<HEADLINE> New Bridge to Be Built in Qijiang of Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Qijiang County in China's
largest metropolis Chongqing, began building a new bridge today to
replace the Rainbow Bridge that collapsed in January this year,
killing 40 people.
</P>
<P>
The notorious incident also led to six million yuan (720,000 U.
S. dollars) in direct economic losses.
</P>
<P>
Investigations discovered that the steel bridge, erected by a
private contractor in February 1996, was of inferior quality, and
the accident resulted from official dereliction of duty and
negligent engineering and construction.
</P>
<P>
The Bridge Engineering Bureau under the Ministry of Railways is
building the New Rainbow Bridge, the contract for which it secured
through public bidding on September 26. It is expected to take 13
months complete the 160-meter-long bridge.  
</P>
</TEXT>
