<HEADLINE> Singapore Shares Rebound Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rebounded
sharply on the Singapore Stock Market Tuesday on improvement of
regional market sentiment a day after plunging below the sensitive
2,000-point mark.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) bounced back to
2,024.44 points with a hike of 34.06 points.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover increased to 226.32 million units valued at
693.85 million Singapore dollars (404.51 million U.S. dollars).
Rises outnumbered falls by 249 to 60 with 148 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was a 32.77 million parcel by Gen Int which
was transacted at 0.335 U.S. dollars per share. The second most
heavily traded stock was SIA which had 23.52 million units done.
AFP was next with 21.84 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH topped the actives chart of the day surging up 90 cents to
close at 27.6 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 ran up 80 cents to
finish at 18.3 Singapore dollars. DBS and SPH 100 climbed by 70
cents to end at 19.4 and 27.6 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, GE Life headed the descent of the day
incurring a loss of 100 cents to close at 15.5 Singapore dollars.
SIA dropped 80 cents to finish at 16.1 Singapore dollars while SIA
200 sank 70 cents and also ended at 16.1 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was encouraged by improved sentiment
across regional bourses which posted a better performance.
</P>
