<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Woos Foreign Investment in Power Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ethiopia's state-owned power industry, which used to be open
only to domestic investors, will issue relevant licenses to
foreign private investors concerned, said Sossaye Mengistu,
General Manager of Ethiopian Electric Power Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The validity of the license for power generation is set at 40
years, while that of power supply will be 50 years, Sossaye was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia, known for its plenty of water resources, is currently
building seven hydro-electric dams across the Horn of Africa
country in hope to more than double its power generation capacity
to 713 megawatts from the current 340 megawatts.
</P>
<P>
The hydro-electric projects are expected to complete in the
next five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
