<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Research Loan to Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) approved Tuesday a 59-million-U.S.-dollar loan to Thailand
for the country's higher education development project.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said in a news release that the aim of the loan is to
produce more scientists and engineers for Thailand to make it more
competitive in the international market.
</P>
<P>
According to the ADB, the project will enable selected
universities to provide postgraduate academic and research
programs in different fields, such as agricultural biotechnology,
chemistry, energy and environment technology.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan will be from the bank's ordinary capital resources
with a maturity period of 25 years, including a grace period of
five years, said the release.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 169.9 million
dollars and the balance of the cost will be borne by the Thai
government, private companies and other sources. 
</P>
