<HEADLINE> 11 Soldiers, Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 28 (Xinhua) -- At least 11 army soldiers and
Tamil rebels were killed in the latest fighting in northern Sri
Lanka, military officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry said four army soldiers were killed
Tuesday morning when Tamil rebels ambushed a route clearing patrol
in Trincomalee district, 250 kilometers northeast of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
It said in a statement that the ambush happened between
Karambagolla and Allakantale, about 60 kilometers west of
Trincomalee.
</P>
<P>
In another incident, military officials said, three soldiers
and four Tamil rebels were killed when the rebels attacked the
forward defense line of the army at Oddusudan in the northern
Wanni region Monday night.
</P>
<P>
They said fighting, including the exchange of mortar fire,
continued till late in the night and there was confrontation on
Tuesday morning as well.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been fighting the government for a Tamil
homeland in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983. 
