<HEADLINE> Photo Album Published For New China's 50th Founding Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A photo album, "Looking at
China from Tian An Men, or the Rostrum of Heavenly Peace" has
appeared in the capital of central-south China's Hunan Province on
the eve of China's national day.
</P>
<P>
The inauguration ceremony to mark for its publication was held
last Saturday at the on-going 10th China Book Fair in the city.
</P>
<P>
It was published by the Sichuan People's Publishing House. It
contains approximately 1,000 valuable photos, mostly of different
views from the Rostrum of Heavenly Peace and the spectacle there
when Chairman Mao Zedong declared the founding of New China on
October 1, 1949.
</P>
<P>
Many of the photos have appeared for the first time in public
and they show to the people an epic historical scroll in the past
50 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
