<HEADLINE> Russia Launches Fresh Air Raids on Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Russian jets launched fresh
air strikes on the breakaway republic of Chechnya Tuesday, the
sixth consecutive day of an intensive campaign aimed at rooting
out Islamic militants there, Russian media reported.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen sorties were flown Monday night and Tuesday morning
against infrastructure targets being used by Chechen militants for
their own ends.
</P>
<P>
Destroyed in the attacks were an oil refinery near Kerla-Yurt,
oil depots in Meskher-Yurt, a power substation four kilometers to
the northeast of Raduzhnoye and a TV center under construction in
the southern outskirts of Grozny, the Interfax news agency
reported, quoting federal forces command headquarters in North
Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
The military noted that the oil refinery and depots were
controlled by Chechen militant leaders who spend part of the
returns from gasoline sales on purchase of weapons and ammunition.
</P>
</TEXT>
