<HEADLINE> Renovation Of Sun Yat-Sen Mausoleum In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- The renovation of the Sun Yat-
Sen Mausoleum in Nanjing, the capital of China's Jiangsu Province,
was completed today.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Sun Yat-Sen (1866-1925) was the founder of the Kuomintang
and provided the inspiration for the revolution that overthrew the
Qing Dynasty (1644-1911).
</P>
<P>
The renovation work started this year to give a new look to his
final resting place and to add some service facilities and flowers
and pine trees to the square in front of the mausoleum.
</P>
<P>
More than five million people from China and abroad are
reported to visit the mausoleum every year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
