<HEADLINE>   Chinese Cyclist Travels across World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese cyclist Monday
arrived in Lusaka, the capital of Zambia, which is the 45th
country he has travelled since he started his current global
travel in March 1997 from Sofia, the capital of Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
To realize his ambition to traval across the world, 42-year-old
Li Yuezhong went to Sofia at the end of 1991 to run a Chinese
restaurant to earn money for the trip.
</P>
<P>
Before coming to Zambia he travelled 44 countries including
Greece, Turkey, Cyprus, Israeli, Egypt, Yugoslavia, Poland,
Hungary, France, Britain, Germany, Morocco, Mauritania, Nigeria
and the Dmocratic Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
During the journey he visited scenic spots, national parks and
historical relics, took pictures and wrote diary.
</P>
<P>
To save money he cooked food with stove or gas burner and
camped in bush and forestry as well as African villages.
</P>
<P>
Li will visit Victoria Fall in Living stone in southern Zambia
and South Luangwa natinal park in Eastern province of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Li also travel widely in African continent before going to
America, Oceania and Asia.
</P>
<P>
He plans to visit 100 countries as China will be his last
destination. And it will take him about three years more.
</P>
<P>
Twenty year ago Li travelled on food between his hometown
Tangshan, in nothern China, and Hangzhou, in southern China. In
early 1980s, he travelled 19 provinces of China on bike. 
</P>
</TEXT>
