<HEADLINE> Chinese Cargo Ship Is Safe: FM Spokeswoman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese cargo ship, which
was attacked by an unidentified armed ship in the waters near Sri
Lanka on September 25, is now safe, according to Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue here today.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, she said that after hearing the news,
the Chinese Embassy in Sri Lanka immediately consulted with the
Sri Lanka side and asked the Sri Lanka government to help with the
matter.
</P>
<P>
With the assistance of the Sri Lanka naval forces, the ship has
sailed to a Sri Lanka port safely.  
</P>
