<HEADLINE> Kenyan Bus Hits Giraffe and Kills 7 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and
10 others seriously injured in a bus accident in Kenya's Central
Province Monday.
</P>
<P>
The bus, which was travelling from the Indian Ocean port
Mombasa to Kenyan capital Nairobi, hit a giraffe, then came out of
control and collided with a lorry.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred shortly after 5 a.m. when the passengers
were in their sleep, according to Tuesday's East African Standard
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is still under investigation, police
sources said, adding that the possible cause was speeding.
</P>
</TEXT>
