CANBERRA -- U.S. Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan had
singled out Australia for praise over the way it weathered the
Asian economic downturn, Australian Prime Minister John Howard
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Greenspan made the comments during a speech to the World Bank/
International Monetary Fund meetings this week in Washington.
