<HEADLINE> Fireworks in HK to Mark China's National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 28 (Xinhua) -- A splendid fireworks
display will light up the sky of Victoria Harbor Friday night to
celebrate the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
A total of 38,388 pieces of fireworks will be discharged from
six barges, and the fireworks display will last for 23 minutes and
be divided into 12 acts, according to a spokesman for the
Provisional Urban Council.
</P>
<P>
Innovation elements will also be added to the display to
provide spectators with completely new experiences, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
The glamour of some fireworks will sustain for 12 seconds after
explosion and will form five layers of multi-color waterfalls, he
said, adding that the grand finale entitled "Millennium Starlight"
will be the climax of the night.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also said that an orchestrated fireworks will
brighten up the entire Victoria Harbor to symbolic Hong Kong's
bright future in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The show can be viewed at various locations on both sides of
the harbor and be broadcast live on television to give the public
the choice of enjoying the fireworks display either on site or at
home, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The event is co-organized by the Provisional Urban Council,
Friends of Hong Kong Association Limited, the Hong Kong Island
Federation, Kowloon Federation of Associations and New Territories
Association of Societies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
