<HEADLINE> India Interested in Ugandan Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Indian entrepreneurs have
expressed interest in the Uganda market and hope to launch joint
ventures with Ugandan businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Managing Director of the Federation of Engineering Industries
of India, Ajay Poddar, said they were eager to invest in Uganda,
particularly in agro-based industries and the petroleum sector.
</P>
<P>
As the head of an Indian trade delegation to Uganda, Poddar met
with Ugandan State Minister for Trade and Industry Vincent Nyanzi
at Farmers' House in Kampala Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Monitor daily Tuesday Poddar as saying that Indian
industries could also come to Uganda and manufacture consumer
products like milk cans and cookers.
</P>
<P>
Nyanzi told the Indian entrepreneurs that Uganda needs
investors who produce for export, and assured them they would be
well facilitated.
</P>
<P>
India is the fifth largest exporter to Uganda and a traditional
trade partner of the east African country. 
</P>
