<HEADLINE> Ningxia Improves Irrigation Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Improvements in the
irrigation system have spurred the economic growth of northwest
China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region over the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
The central government has invested more than one billion yuan
in building and upgrading Ningxia's irrigation works since New
China was founded in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The region's farmland acreage has been increased to 400,000
hectares from only 128,000 hectares in 1949. The Qingtongxia water-
control project alone has added 113,000 hectares of irrigated
farmland to Ningxia's total.
</P>
<P>
This brought about a 12.2-fold increase in the region's grain
output, which reached more than two billion kilograms last year.
</P>
<P>
And over the past 50 years, the per hectare rice output has
risen to 9,000 kilograms from 3,000 kilograms, and wheat, from 735
kilograms to 6,000 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia has vowed to become an important agricultural and
sideline-commodities production base by boosting its pillar
industries including grain, animal husbandry, wine, biological
pharmaceuticals, and fruits and vegetables, authorities note.
</P>
<P>
To achieve this goal, farmland acreage will reach 670,000
hectares, they say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
