<HEADLINE> Northern California fires Destroy 30 Homes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 27 (Xinhua) -- Wind-fanned flames Monday
destroyed more than 30 homes and forced hundreds of residents to
evacuate from a rural area of Northern California, according to
local reports.
</P>
<P>
The fire started Sunday morning as three separate blazes that
merged together, officials said. The cause was not known.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Forestry said 37 dwellings, 43 outbuildings
and 15 vehicles were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters are still battling a series of blazes in
California's Trinity Alps Wilderness that have scorched more than
60,000 acres.
</P>
<P>
On the central California coast, another group of fires had
burned 42,454 acres in the Ventana Wilderness of Los Padres
National Forest.
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said it will take weeks to contain two of those
fires. 
</P>
