<HEADLINE> Plant Disease And Pests Plaguing Northern Chinese Forests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Warm temperatures are being
blamed for the increase in plant disease and insect pests that
have been plaguing 2.4 million ha. of forests in China's Shanxi
Province in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The plant diseases and pests have reportedly spread next door
to Henan Province, threatening 10 million ha. of Chinese pines.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 3.4 million trees are covered with brown-spot and
caterpillars and reported dead in Shanxi alone. Some measures have
been tried in the fight against the plant disease and pests.
</P>
<P>
China has 134 million hectares of forests, or only 8.6 hectares
per capita, much lower than the world average. 
</P>
