<HEADLINE> Bell Cast to Mark New Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Workers have begun casting
a 6.8-meter-high bell, weighing 50 tons to mark the advent of the
new century.
</P>
<P>
The bell will be decorated with a depiction of major historical
events in China over the past century and inscribed with the
national anthem, as well as 56 peony flowers symbolizing the unity
and friendship of China's 56 ethnic groups and two huge dragons
representing the Yangtze and Yellow rivers. The bell was designed
by Professor Xiao Hong of Henan University.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing municipal government has set aside nearly 1,300
square meters at the All-China Century Temple, now being built in
the western part of the city, as the site for the bell.  
