<HEADLINE> Thai Police Seize 904,000 Speed Pills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Thai police seized 904,000
methamphtamine pills and arrested eight suspects in two raids over
the weekend, the Bangkok Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, police searched a car at a toll plaza near Bangkok
and found 470,000 pills in a suitcase in the car's boot. The two
suspects were charged with trafficking narcotics.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, six men were rounded up in Bangkok and charged with
possessing 434,000 speed pills with intent to sell.
</P>
<P>
The Narcotics Suppression Bureau said it has seized 5.9 million
speed pills, 104 kilograms of heroin, 42 kilograms of cannabis and
159 ecstasy pills since January.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the Office of the Narcotics Control
Board also confiscated some 25 million speed pills. It expects to
seize five million more. 
