Lamar Alexander and Senator Bob Smith of New Hampshire dropped out
of the Republican primary contest earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Republican presidential front-runner George W. Bush has raised
more than 50 million U.S. dollars so far in the campaign while
Quayle had raised only 4 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, among the remaining candidates, Arizona Senator John
McCain formally kicked off his campaign Monday with a speech at
the Naval Academy in Annapolis, Maryland. 
