<HEADLINE> Plovdiv Technical Fair Attracts Record Number of Participants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The 55th International
Technical Fair of Plovdiv, which opened in Bulgaria's second
largest city of Plovdiv Monday, has attracted a record number of 1,
925 participants from 41 countries.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that "the fair has not been that good since
1985," Bulgaria's Trade and Tourism Minister Valentin Vassilev was
quoted as saying by the local media.
</P>
<P>
The exposition includes 18 pavilions and open air exhibition
areas surrounding the pavilions for a total of 90,000 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
Most of the exhibits consist of industrial machines,
information technology and transport and service sectors.
</P>
<P>
The major foreign participants include Germany, Austria, the
United States, the Czech Republic, Italy and Poland.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo crisis and the financial problems in Russia and in
other Commonwealth of Independent States countries have had some
adverse effects on the Plovdiv fair's preparation, Vassilev said
at the opening ceremony. 
