<HEADLINE> China Develops World's Tiniest Helicopter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 28 (Xinhua)-- The tiniest unmanned
helicopter in the world was recently developed at Shanghai
Jiaotong University (SJU) by nanometer technology reseachers.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter is 18 mm long, 5 mm high, 3 mm wide, and weighs
100 mg. It takes off and lands in a space of two peanuts. It is
powered by an alternating current motor.
</P>
<P>
Development of the helicopter involves the study of special
materials, micro-machining techniques, electronics and
aerodynamics and the technology is expected to be used for
reconnaissance purpose.  
</P>
