<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Remains High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 27 (Xinhua) -- The average price of the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Country's basket of seven
crudes remained at a high of 22.3 U.S. dollars per barrel last
week, the Vienna-based OPEC Secretariat announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
The oil Cartel's average oil price over the week was basically
on a par with the previous week's average of 22.31 U.S. dollars
per barrel.
</P>
<P>
Since OPEC oil ministers reached an agreement to cut production
to shore up prices in March, the organization's average oil price
has more than doubled, exceeding its benchmark price of 21 U.S.
dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
On September 22, the OPEC oil ministers decided that the daily
oil production ceilings imposed on its member countries will
continue to be implemented until the end of March next year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predict that oil prices on the international oil
market will continue to soar in the winter of this year, to an
expected high of 25 to 28 U.S. dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
OPEC uses the basket of seven crudes to monitor the oil market
supply. 
</P>
</TEXT>
