<HEADLINE> Chongqing Introduces Legal Consultation Hotline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing Municipality in
southwest China introduced a new free legal consultation hotline
number (160-0148) today.
</P>
<P>
The first such hotline (148) opened last June in Dongming
County of Heze Prefecture in east China's Shandong Province. To
date, 207 cities and 2,561 counties nationwide have opened similar
hotlines.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing opened a trial legal hotline in Yongchuan County on
January 1 this year, and over 8,853 people have since requested
advice. Some 3,384 people have received door-to-door services on
legal affairs, avoiding six million yuan in economic losses.
</P>
<P>
Officials note that most calls involve disputes over housing,
labor, and debts and marriage. Chongqing residents have expressed
satisfaction with the convenient and cost-free service. 
</P>
