<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 1,000 Houses Destroyed by Tornado in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Over 1,000 houses were
completely destroyed and 10,000 persons were adversely affected
as a tornado accompanied by strong winds hit Medirigiriya in the
Polonnaruwa district of Sri Lanka last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 500 houses were completely flattened when the tornado
estimated at 50 miles per hour hit four villages within two to
three minutes, media sources here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 shops and government offices in the area, about
260 kilometers from Colombo, were also completely destroyed.
</P>
<P>
They said strong winds accompanied by thunder and heavy showers
hit the area around 4.30 p.m. on Sunday, uprooting many trees and
lamp posts.
</P>
<P>
Within three minutes all the roads were covered with debris due
to the deluge which affected the drainage, electricity and
telecommunication systems, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Total damage has not yet been estimated.
</P>
<P>
Local government has taken relief action by providing dry
rations to the affected people. Volunteers from neighboring areas
have started clearing the roads and compensation is to be paid to
those affected.
</P>
<P>
The tornado was a result of thunder showers crossing monsoon
winds, according to Sri Lankan Meteorological Department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
